03/11/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin will visit Bulgaria on November 13th, Prime Minister Boyko Borisov announced on Tuesday (November 2nd), following a phone conversation late Monday. 
During their talks in Sofia, Borisov and Putin will discuss joint energy projects such as the Belene nuclear power plant and the South Stream project, as well as the price of Russian gas supplies to Bulgaria. 
Ways to boost trade between the two countries will also be discussed. 
Bulgaria and Russia are due to sign an agreement to establish a joint company for the South Stream project on November 15th. 
(Darik, Focus - 02/11/10)
